5:
Wait... Something's not right! I can still 
sense Orochi!
9:
Oooh! I'm honestly impressed you 
managed to cut off all eight heads!
...It would certainly be a shame if NONE 
of that mattered!
11:
Weren't you listening to Izumi? Orochi 
is invincible! I've still got THOUSANDS of 
souls to revive it with! Do your worst, 
darlings. I'll wait.
19:
Alk, Stella, I need you to listen. Take 
Inaho, and run. Go!
23: Run?! What, and leave you behind?!
27:
I can't recast the Circle of Corrosion. 
We're done for...
30:
What's to say it would have fixed 
anything anyways? It's even more 
destructive than Orochi. I failed…
 I never had a chance from the start.
39:
Pathetic! What happened to the smug, 
condescending, arrogant, stuck-up 
JERK I know?
43:
Hmph! So much for being a big fancy 
diviner! You are merely a big fat 
CRYBABY! Stop being a poopie-head 
and help!
46:
A-a poopie... head?
I would have handled the situation just 
fine if YOU hadn't—
51:
You would have died! Now help me—
we can use the power of the Nine Tails, 
but I cannot do it alone!
54: The power of the Nine Tails?
57:
The masked woman used my power to 
summon Orochi. Surely there must be 
some way to make it go away!
60:
It's not that simple! Your power broke 
the seal on Orochi, like punching 
a hole through a wall. If we use it again, 
we'll set loose ALL the—
64: We'll... We'll set loose all the spirits.
68:
There must be SOMETHING I can do to 
help! I love Yamato! I love the yokai 
and all the humans too!
70: Please, let me save you! Please!
74:
You're asking for permission to save 
us? An odd request, but seeing as you 
asked so nicely—
77:
I have a plan. We must destroy the 
seal and release the spirits.
82:
Release the spirits? Are you out of your 
mind?! Why?!
85:
They are the source of Orochi's 
immortality. As long as Orochi cannot 
access the spirits, it doesn't matter 
whether we destroy them or simply 
relocate them.
87:
If we destroy the seal, the currents of 
energy will guide the tide of spirits 
down the peaks, back to the land 
where they belong.
89:
Stella, I will need your help, as well. 
Will you lend me your aid?
93: I will. What should I do?
95:
I'll need you to break the seal, like how 
you broke my Circle of Corrosion.
109:
Normal foxes belong to the elemental 
domain of earth, but you... You're 
different. I sense the energy of metal in 
your power. Please, lend that power to 
me!
112:
My mother IS called the "golden" fox! 
I shall lend you all the power you need!
114:
Then let us begin.
Circle of Growth!
118: From the earth, is found metal.
122: Metal resists water, and carries it far.
126:
Water nourishes trees, and begets 
wood.
131:
Did you think I'd just sit on my hands 
and wait for you to finish? Enough!
141:
Alk?! Why?!
Why do you stand in my way?!
152:
Wood feeds fire, and fire turns all to 
ashes—returning them to the earth!
Thunder bloom, lightning blossom!
...Stella, NOW!
162: So much for Orochi. A pity.
164:
I thought the two of us had something 
SPECIAL.
Oh well, no sense crying over spilled 
milk.
167: The sorceress... looks just like Stella?!
171: I-I don't understand! Who ARE you?!
175:
Who, me? Why, I'm Stella of course!
Right, Stella dear?
182:
You wouldn't, would you? It doesn't 
matter, really. I suppose you win this 
time.
186:
But I WILL say you've squandered 
a great deal of time running around 
playing hero.
188:
Can you afford to dawdle, Light? How's 
that princess of yours doing?
...I bet you have no idea! Do you even 
care?
194:
Save it. You'd better get a move on, 
darling. Don't blame ME if you're too 
late!
203:
Wait!
She didn't explain anything... Who is 
she?
214:
You three are safe now! Guess what! 
We have defeated Orochi—and 
I helped!
218:
Wooow! You're so strong, Princess 
Inaho!
228:
Indeed. You all did well. For now, try to 
focus on the present. You have done 
these lands a great service—celebrate 
it!
